dataIdInfo.idPurp: Aggregated predicted stream flow for perennial and ephemeral streams within the Santa Ana watershed under reference conditions. Reference conditions are defined as having no or minimal anthropogenically modified/influenced contributing factors upstream. Predictions have been generated by inputting a number of climate and landscape variables into a statistical model that has been developed using the R statistical software package. Values presented within the attribute table have been aggregated from 30m2 resolution raster data by averaging values that coincide with a given NHDPlus COMID value.
